key-wdi2-PX.REX.REER.def: Real effective exchange rate is the nominal effective exchange rate (a measure of the value of a currency against a weighted average of several foreign currencies) divided by a price deflator or index of costs.
key-wdi2-PX.REX.REER.name: Real effective exchange rate index
key-wdi2-PX.REX.REER.source: International Monetary Fund, International Financial Statistics.
